    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>What are you going to do with the URI?</p>\n\n<p>If you're just going to use it with an HttpGet for example, you can just use the string directly when creating the HttpGet instance.</p>\n\n<pre><code>HttpGet get = new HttpGet(\"http://stackoverflow.com\");\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6678582,
      "reputation" : 3477,
      "user_id" : 5152497,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 57,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d7520538e6b947b5d056912c5e168088?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "J&#252;rgen K.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5152497/j%c3%bcrgen-k"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 56,
    "last_activity_date" : 1610460065,
    "last_edit_date" : 1610460065,
    "creation_date" : 1442934655,
    "answer_id" : 32720540,
    "question_id" : 3487389,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am just using the <code>java.net</code> <strong>package</strong>.\nHere you can do the following:</p>\n<pre><code>...\nimport java.net.URI;\n...\n\nString myUrl = &quot;http://stackoverflow.com&quot;;\nURI myURI = new URI(myUrl);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1292258,
      "reputation" : 11906,
      "user_id" : 1244127,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/7S9Fd.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "JSON C11",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1244127/json-c11"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1484079637,
    "last_edit_date" : 1484079637,
    "creation_date" : 1484079078,
    "answer_id" : 41577518,
    "question_id" : 3487389,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can parse a String to a Uri by using <strong><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/net/Uri.html#parse(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Uri.parse()</a></strong> as shown below:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Uri myUri = Uri.parse(\"http://stackoverflow.com\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The following is an example of how you can use your newly created Uri in an implicit intent. To be viewed in a browser on the users phone.</p>\n\n<pre><code>// Creates a new Implicit Intent, passing in our Uri as the second paramater.\nIntent webIntent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW, myUri);\n\n// Checks to see if there is an Activity capable of handling the intent\nif (webIntent.resolveActivity(getPackageManager()) != null){\n    startActivity(webIntent);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>NB:</strong> There is a difference between Androids <strong><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/net/URI.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">URI</a></strong> and <strong><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/net/Uri.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Uri</a></strong>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 279796,
      "reputation" : 84,
      "user_id" : 3858815,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2f2b45e3f6b18b6ebd30e93d3d9072e4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "EricE",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3858815/erice"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1510519036,
    "creation_date" : 1510519036,
    "answer_id" : 47253691,
    "question_id" : 3487389,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java's parser in <code>java.net.URI</code> is going to fail if the URI isn't fully encoded to its standards. For example, try to parse: <code>http://www.google.com/search?q=cat|dog</code>. An exception will be thrown for the vertical bar.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/EricEdens/urllib\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">urllib</a> makes it easy to convert a string to a <code>java.net.URI</code>. It will pre-process and escape the URL. </p>\n\n<pre><code>assertEquals(\"http://www.google.com/search?q=cat%7Cdog\",\n    Urls.createURI(\"http://www.google.com/search?q=cat|dog\").toString());\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4250277,
      "reputation" : 3027,
      "user_id" : 3477577,
      "user_type" : "registered",
